victimize /ˈvɪktɪˌmaɪz/

(victimizing,victimized,victimizes) BRIT also  victimise 

1. V-T If someone is victimized , they are deliberately treated unfairly. 受迫害 

例： He felt the students had been victimized because they'd voiced opposition to the government. 他认为学生们因发表反对政府的言论而受到了迫害。 

2. victimization N-UNCOUNT 迫害 

例： ...society's cruel victimization of women. …社会对妇女的残酷迫害。

